<li class=3D"cue-slide" id=3D"slide-497">
<div>
<p><strong>Example 1:</strong> In a =CE=94LMN, =E2=88=A0N =3D 3=E2=88=A0M =
=3D 2(=E2=88=A0L+=E2=88=A0M). Calculate the angles of =CE=94LMN using this =
information.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Let =E2=88=A0L =3D x=C2=B0 and =E2=88=A0M =3D y=C2=B0.</p>
<p>Then,</p>
<p>=E2=88=A0N =3D 3=E2=88=A0M =3D (3y)=C2=B0.</p>
<p>Now,</p>
<p>=E2=88=A0L + =E2=88=A0M + =E2=88=A0N =3D 180=C2=B0<br>
	=E2=88=B4 x + y + 3y =3D 180<br>
	x + 4y =3D 180 ... (1)<br>
	From the given equation, 3=E2=88=A0M =3D 2(=E2=88=A0L+=E2=88=A0M)<br>
	=E2=88=B4 3y =3D 2(x + y) =E2=87=92 2x - y =3D 0 ... (2)<br>
	On multiplying (2) by 4 and adding the result to (1), we get<br>
	9x =3D 180<br>
	x =3D 20<br>
	Substitute this in (2):<br>
	40 - y =3D 0 =E2=87=92 y =3D 40<br>
	Therefore, =E2=88=A0L =3D 20=C2=B0 and =E2=88=A0M =3D 40=C2=B0.<br>
	Therefore, the third angle is, =E2=88=A0N =3D 180 - (20 + 40) =3D 120=C2=
=B0.<br>
<strong>Answer:</strong> =E2=88=A0L =3D 20=C2=B0, =E2=88=A0M =3D 40=C2=B0, =
and =E2=88=A0N =3D 120=C2=B0.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class=3D"cue-slide" id=3D"slide-469">
<div>
<p><strong>Example 2:</strong> Peter is three times as old as his son. 5 ye=
ars later, he shall be two and half times as old as his son. What's Peter's=
 present age?</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Let Peter's age be x years and his son's age be y years. Then by given i=
nfo,</p>
<p>x =3D 3y ... (1)</p>
<p>5 years later,</p>
<p>Peter's age =3D x + 5 years and his son's age =3D y + 5 years.</p>
<p>By the given condition,</p>
<p>x + 5 =3D 5/2 (y + 5)</p>
<p>2x - 5y - 15 =3D 0 ... (2)</p>
<p>From (1), we have x =3D 3y. Substitute this in (2):</p>
<p>2(3y) - 5y - 15 =3D 0</p>
<p>y =3D 15</p>
<p>Substitute this in (1): x =3D 3(15) =3D 45</p>
<p>Thus, the solution of the given system is (x, y) =3D (45, 15).</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Present age of Peter =3D 45 years; Present age =
of son =3D 15 years.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class=3D"cue-slide" id=3D"slide-577">
<div>
<p><strong>Example 3:</strong> Tressa starts her job with a certain monthly=
 salary and earns a fixed increment every year. If her salary was $1500 aft=
er 4 years and $1800 after 10 years of service, find her starting salary an=
d annual increment.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Let her starting salary be x and annual increment be y.</p>
<p>After 4 years, her salary was $1500</p>
<p>x + 4y =3D 1500 ... (1)</p>
<p>After 10 years, her salary was $1800</p>
<p>x + 10y =3D 1800 ... (2)</p>
<p>Subtracting Eqn (1) from (2), we get</p>
<p>6y =3D 300</p>
<p>=E2=88=B4 y =3D 50</p>
<p>On putting y =3D 50 in (1), we get x =3D 1300.</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Starting salary was $1300 and annual increment =
is $50.</p>
</div>
</li>
