div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" ite=
mtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">How Do You=
 Solve a System of Equations?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggested=
Answer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schem=
a.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>Solving a system of equations is co=
mputing the unknown variables still balancing the equations on both sides. =
We solve an equation system to find the values of the variables that satisf=
y the condition of all the given equations. There are different methods to =
solve a system of equations,</p><ul>
<li>Graphical method</li>
<li>Substitution method</li>
<li>Elimination method</li>
<li>Cross-multiplication method</li>
</ul></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" ite=
mprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=
=3D"name text">How Do You Create a System of Equations with Two Variables?<=
/h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=
=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=
=3D"text"><p>To create a system of equations with two variables:</p><ul>
<li>First, identify the two unknown quantities in the given problem.</li>
<li>Next, find out the two conditions given and frame equations for each of=
 them.</li>
</ul></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" ite=
mprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=
=3D"name text">How to Solve a System of Equations by Substitution Method?</=
h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D=
"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"=
text"><p>The substitution method is one of the ways to solve a system of eq=
uations in two variables, given the set of linear equations. In this method=
, we substitute the value of a variable found by one equation in the second=
 equation.</p></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-ques=
tion" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 =
itemprop=3D"name text">How to Solve a System of Equations Using the Elimina=
tion Method?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAn=
swer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><di=
v itemprop=3D"text"><p>The elimination method is used to solve a system of =
linear equations. In the elimination method, we eliminate one of the two va=
riables by multiplying each equation with the required numbers and try to s=
olve equations with another variable. In this process, finding <a href=3D"h=
ttps://www.cuemath.com/numbers/lcm-least-common-multiple/">LCM</a> of coeff=
icients would be helpful.</p></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D=
"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org=
/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">What is the Purpose of Graphing Syste=
ms of Equations?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer accept=
edAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"=
><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>To solve the system of equations, given a set of=
 linear equations graphically, we need to find at least two solutions for t=
he respective equations. We observe the pattern of lines after plotting the=
 points to infer it is consistent, dependent, or inconsistent.</p><ul>
<li>If the two lines are intersecting at the same point, then the intersect=
ion point gives a unique solution for the system of equations.</li>
<li>If the two lines coincide, then in this case there are infinitely many =
solutions.</li>
<li>If the two lines are parallel, then in this case there is no solution.<=
/li>
</ul></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" ite=
mprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=
=3D"name text">What are Homogeneous System of Linear Equations?</h3><div it=
emscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed=
-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>T=
he homogeneous system of linear equations is a set of linear equation each =
one of which has its constant term to be 0. The process of solving these ki=
nd of systems can be learnt in detailed by clicking <a href=3D"https://www.=
cuemath.com/algebra/homogeneous-system-of-linear-equations/">here</a>.</p><=
/div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=
=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"na=
me text">How to Solve a System of Equations With Cross Multiplication Metho=
d?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" clas=
s=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=
=3D"text"><p>While solving a system of equations using the <a href=3D"https=
://www.cuemath.com/algebra/cross-multiplication-method/">cross-multiplicati=
on method</a>, we use the formula x / (b<sub>1</sub>c<sub>2</sub> - b<sub>2=
</sub>c<sub>1</sub>) =3D -y / (a<sub>1</sub>c<sub>2</sub> - a<sub>2</sub>c<=
sub>1</sub>) =3D 1 / (a<sub>1</sub>b<sub>2</sub> - a<sub>2</sub>b<sub>1</su=
b>) to solve the system a<sub>1</sub>x + b<sub>1</sub>y + c<sub>1</sub> =3D=
 0 and a<sub>2</sub>x + b<sub>2</sub>y + c<sub>2</sub> =3D 0.</p></div></di=
v></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEn=
tity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">H=
ow do you Solve a System of Equations Using 2 Equations with 3 Variables?</=
h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D=
"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"=
text"><p>An equation with 3 variables represents a <a href=3D"https://www.c=
uemath.com/geometry/plane-definition/">plane</a>.</p><ul>
<li>Step 1) To solve a system of 2 equations with 3 variables say x, y, and=
 z, we will consider the 1st two equations and eliminate one of the variabl=
es, say x, to obtain a new equation.</li>
<li>Step 2) Next, we write the 2nd variable, y in terms of z from the new e=
quation and substitute it in the third equation.</li>
<li>Step 3) Assuming z =3D a, we will obtain values of x and y also in term=
s of 'a'.</li>
<li>Step 4) Once, we know the value of a, we can find the values of x and y=
 in terms of 'a'.</li>
</ul></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" ite=
mprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=
=3D"name text">What is the Solution to the System of Equations and How to F=
